        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer64685884" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1560893776884333757">I liked this book. There isn&apos;t any wild climatic events that you may find in other Grisham books. This is a simple novel of a simple life as told by a seven year old boy. Still, Grisham manages to capture the feelings of the times; a poor family in the south who hire workers to harvest their cotton and the drama that ensues with these &quot;lower class&quot; folk. I can see why a lot of Grisham fans wouldn&apos;t like this, it&apos;s a departure from his normal genre. </span>
  <span id="freeText1560893776884333757" style="display:none">I liked this book. There isn't any wild climatic events that you may find in other Grisham books. This is a simple novel of a simple life as told by a seven year old boy. Still, Grisham manages to capture the feelings of the times; a poor family in the south who hire workers to harvest their cotton and the drama that ensues with these "lower class" folk. I can see why a lot of Grisham fans wouldn't like this, it's a departure from his normal genre. </span>
