              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15709492737806347951">I like Grisham&apos;s legal thrillers on occasion, and I love SKIPPING CHRISTMAS. This is an altogether different beast. Straight up historical fiction, set on a struggling cotton farm in 1950&apos;s Arkansas, it&apos;s as much a picture of that time and place as it is a coming of age tale. I would recommend this to teens, I think it would be great for classroom discussion. It&apos;s a sort of post-Depression, Grapes of Wrath-lite. </span>
  <span id="freeText15709492737806347951" style="display:none">I like Grisham's legal thrillers on occasion, and I love SKIPPING CHRISTMAS. This is an altogether different beast. Straight up historical fiction, set on a struggling cotton farm in 1950's Arkansas, it's as much a picture of that time and place as it is a coming of age tale. I would recommend this to teens, I think it would be great for classroom discussion. It's a sort of post-Depression, Grapes of Wrath-lite. </span>
